Marcus Says South African Economic Outlook Poses ‘Challenges’ From Oil

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-05-24T15:39:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/marcus-says-south-african-economic-outlook-poses-challenges-from-oil.html
South Africa ’s economic outlook poses
“challenges,” mainly because of rising food and oil prices,
Reserve Bank Governor Gill Marcus said.  While the economy is out of recession, it is still in
“crisis,” Marcus said at the Monetary Policy Forum in  Pretoria 
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
